 because Python can check the expression directly.


python does nto need a variable name to calculate something ! 

1 + 1

this is an expression ! 

python sees 

1 + 1 == 2

and evaluates each step 

1 + 1          → 2
2 == 2         → True
assert True    → pass


so 

def test_pytest_is_working():
    assert 1 + 1 == 2


means:

“Check that the expression 1 + 1 == 2 becomes True.”




